# Output Format

Produce a **Structured Input** document in the following markdown format:

```markdown
# Structured Input
## Project Type
<fullstack | frontend_only | backend_only>
## Frontend Kind
<web | cli | desktop | mobile | none>
## Feature Requirements
- [F001] <feature name>: <description>
- [F002] ...
## Preferences
### Tech Stack
- Frontend: <framework>
- Backend: <framework>
- Database: <database>
### Deployment
- Frontend: <service>
- Backend: <service>
### Plugins & Skills
- <plugin>: <usage>
### UI/UX Preferences
- <preference>
### Patterns & Conventions
- <pattern or convention discovered from existing codebase, if any>
```

**Project type rules:**
- `fullstack` — The project has both a user-facing surface (web, CLI, desktop, or mobile) and a custom backend.
- `frontend_only` — The project has only a user-facing surface — no custom backend. This includes apps that use a Backend-as-a-Service (BaaS) like Supabase, Firebase, or Convex; the BaaS replaces a custom backend. Also includes standalone CLIs, desktop apps, and mobile apps with no custom server.
- `backend_only` — The project has only a backend: an API, library, or service with no user-facing surface at all.
- When in doubt, default to `fullstack`.

**Frontend kind rules:**
- `web` — A web app (browser-based). Use this for React/Vue/Next/Svelte/etc.
- `cli` — A command-line tool invoked from a shell. Use this for `typer`, `click`, `cobra`, Bubble Tea, etc.
- `desktop` — A desktop app. Use this for Tauri or Electron applications.
- `mobile` — A mobile app. Use this for React Native (Expo) or Flutter.
- `none` — Only valid when `Project Type` is `backend_only`. Indicates there is no user-facing surface at all.
- If the user specifies the finer stack (e.g. "React Native" vs "Flutter"), record it under Preferences > Tech Stack while keeping the Frontend Kind coarse-grained.

If the user did not specify a preference, omit that line rather than guessing. Keep feature descriptions concise but complete. Each feature should represent a distinct, testable piece of functionality.
